cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with extending the classical LTL synthesis problem to a quantitative setting, and proposes a new problem called LTLMP synthesis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm to automatically construct a reactive system that satisfies a given LTL formula and has mean-payoff values greater than or equal to some given threshold. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper deals with synthesizing reactive systems from LTL specifications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes a Safraless procedure to decide whether there exists a finite-memory strategy that realizes a given specification for some given threshold, which involves solving two-player energy safety games and safety games. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possible category as the paper deals with LTL synthesis, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory.
